    "privileged_info_summary": "The tip_pool_calculator@1 task uses synthetic data for a restaurant tip distribution scenario. Five staff members (Alice: 8.5 hours, Bob: 6.0 hours, Carlos: 7.5 hours, Diana: 4.0 hours, Emma: 5.5 hours, totaling 31.5 hours) must have pooled tips ($287.50 cash + $312.00 credit = $599.50 total) distributed proportionally based on hours worked. The verification system checks 6 equally-weighted criteria (16.67% each): total tips calculation, total hours calculation, percentage calculations with absolute cell references, tip share calculations with absolute references, conservation law (distributed ≈ collected within $0.50), and formula presence. A score of 70% (4 out of 6 criteria) is required to pass. The task allows 180 seconds and 20 maximum steps with sparse reward feedback.",
